<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Configure the associated emergency exit sign, floor proximity escape path markings and passenger seats as appropriate (AMM DDG 52-11-01). </Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Cover the emergency exit signs unique to the inoperative door.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Cover the floor proximity escape path marking system lights unique to the inoperative door.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Block the inoperative door with conspicuous barrier strap or rope and placard door is inoperative.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Block off the affected passenger seats with conspicuous tapes or ropes and placard seats are not to be occupied by passengers.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
<OperationProcedure>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Added additional wording to allow for dispatch flexibility.">
<?FTID-rev start?>Arming of the passenger entry doors using the mode select handles in the automatic position (red band) prior to taxi, takeoff and
landing whenever passengers are carried includes the inoperative door, whenever possible, with or without the escape slide removed.<?FTID-rev end?></Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Flight crew members and passengers must be briefed prior to takeoff and landing regarding the inoperative door that cannot be used for emergency evacuation.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Cabin crew briefing to Passengers in emergency evacuation: In event of an emergency evacuation, subject to door inoperative, Cabin crew will brief passengers to use appropriate doors as follows:</Para>
