<DispatchCondition dispCondOptions="B" repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="8" nbrRequired="4" maintIndicator="(M)" opsIndicator="(O)">
<Title>
<?FTID-xref 1221610.2-52-11-01_FAA?>No Passengers Carried</Title>
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>May be inoperative or slide missing provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>No passengers are carried.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>A maximum of 19 persons authorized by VAR for non-passenger carrying operations are carried.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>A conspicuous barrier strap or rope and a placard stating that the door is inoperative shall be placed across the inoperative door.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Emergency exit sign and floor proximity lights associated with the inoperative exit must be covered to obscure the sign and lights.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Inoperative doors are not used for loading.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Each person carried has unobstructed access from their seat to an operative door.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Safety briefing includes location of inoperative doors and instructions not to use them.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Operations procedure is used.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceProcedure>
<Para>Block the inoperative doors with conspicuous barrier strap or rope and placard as inoperative, configure the associated emergency exit signs and floor proximity escape path markings as appropriate (AMM DDG 52-11-01). </Para>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Block the inoperative doors with conspicuous barrier strap or rope and placard as inoperative.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Cover the emergency exit signs unique to the inoperative doors.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Cover the floor proximity escape path marking system lights unique to the inoperative doors.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</MaintenanceProcedure>
<OperationProcedure>
<List listType="1.">
<ListItem rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Added additional wording to allow for dispatch flexibility">
<Para>No passengers may be carried.</Para>
<?FTID-rev start?>
<?FTID-rev end?>
</ListItem>
<ListItem rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Added additional wording to allow for dispatch flexibility">
<Para>A maximum of 19 persons may be carried.</Para>
<?FTID-rev start?>
<?FTID-rev end?>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Inoperative doors are not to be used for loading.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Flight crew members and authorized persons must be briefed prior to takeoff and landing regarding the inoperative doors that cannot be used for emergency evacuation.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para rev:revStatus="R" rev:revHighlight="Added additional wording to allow for dispatch flexibility.">
<?FTID-rev start?>Arming of the passenger entry doors using the mode select handles in the automatic position (red band) prior to taxi, takeoff and landing includes the inoperative
doors, whenever possible, with or without the escape slide removed.<?FTID-rev end?></Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</OperationProcedure>
</DispatchProcedure>
